===Etymology===
From {{der|en|la|dēnigrātus}}, the past participle of {{m|la|dēnigrāre||to blacken}}, from {{m|la|dē}} + {{m|la|nigrare||to blacken}} (from {{m|la|niger||black}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈdɛn.ɪ.ɡɹeɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-denigrate.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-au-denigrate.ogg|Audio (AU)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|denigrat}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[criticise]] so as to [[besmirch]]; [[traduce]], [[disparage]] or [[defame]].
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To treat as [[worthless]]; [[belittle]], [[degrade]] or [[disparage]].
#: {{ux|en|You have no right to '''denigrate''' people and things that you have no personal experience with.}}
# {{lb|en|rare}} To [[blacken]]. <!-- this usage is the literal sense, yet obscure at best -->

